{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0113242uNnMXXKrYv5spuTSH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the source file and convert it to a knowledge file following the work steps.\n\n**Step 1: Title**\nThe first heading underlined with `=====` is: `入力画面と確認画面の共通化をサポートするカスタムタグ`\n\n**Step 1.5: Check for no-knowledge-content**\nThe source has explanatory text, code examples, and implementation guidance. It has Layer A and Layer B content. Set `no_knowledge_content: false`.\n\n**Step 2: Build section list**\nExpected Sections provided:\n- (empty/root section - the intro section)\n- 入力画面と確認画面の表示切り替え\n\n\n- (empty - possibly usage examples like パスワードの使用例, 携帯電話番号の使用例, ボタンの使用例)\n- 確認画面での入力項目の表示\n\nLooking at the Expected Sections structure with 4 entries where some are empty, the file ID ending in `--s1` suggests this is the first section of a larger document, so I need to map the actual content sections to these placeholders. I'm parsing through the RST heading structure to understand the document hierarchy. The file contains multiple sections marked by different underline characters—equals signs for the title and dashes for subsections—and I need to map out how these headings correspond to the expected section splits (s1 through s4). I'm analyzing how the document structure maps to the expected sections list. The classification detected four sections: an intro without a heading, the input/confirmation screen toggle section, what appears to be a grouped usage examples section (possibly without a direct heading), and the confirmation screen display items section. I'll map these to the expected sections array and create the corresponding section identifiers. I see now — the file ID `--s1` indicates this is section 1 of the overall file, but within this knowledge file there are 4 internal sections labeled s1 through s4. So the Expected Sections are breaking down the content into those 4 parts: the intro, the input/confirmation screen toggle section, what looks like usage examples, and then the confirmation screen display section. The third section being empty in the Expected Sections output is probably where the usage examples for password and phone number live, just grouped separately from the main section heading.\n\nLooking at the RST markup more carefully, I can see the hierarchy — the h2 level headers are underlined with dashes, and then the usage examples like パスワードの使用例 are underlined with equals signs, which would make them a different heading level in this context. Looking at the RST structure, I can see there's another h3 section for button examples, followed by an h2 heading about displaying input items on the confirmation screen. So the document has at least two main h2 sections with the first one containing multiple h3 subsections underneath it. Looking at the structure, I'm seeing that the sections break down into an intro covering the confirmationPage tag's purpose, followed by a section on toggling between input and confirmation screens. The key insight is that when input and confirmation screens map one-to-one, you can reduce development effort by consolidating the JSP creation—the implementation sharing happens in the input screen's JSP while the confirmation screen just forwards to it, with each action handling its respective screen separately. 次のセクションでは、使用例として パスワード、携帯電話番号、ボタンのコード例を示しており、上記のタグで対応できない場合は入力・確認画面のJSPを分けて開発することを推奨している。また、確認画面での入力項目の表示について、全画面共通ヘッダに検索フォームを配置する場合の注意点と、ignoreConfirmationタグを使用して画面内の一部分を常に入力項目として表示する方法を説明している。\n\n入力画面と確認画面が1対1に対応する場合、共通化により確認画面JSPの作成工数を削減できるため、実装の共通化は入力画面のJSPで行い、確認画面のJSPは入力画面のJSPにフォワードのみ行う。アクションは入力・確認それぞれ別JSPにフォワードしておくことで、仕様変更時のアクションへの影響を抑えられ、確認画面のJSPはWebView_ConfirmationPageTagを使用してフォワードを行う。\n\n入力・確認画面のJSPは同じ場所に配置することが多いため、相対パスで指定できる。\n\n表示切り替えにはWebView_ForInputPageTagとWebView_ForConfirmationPageTagを使用し、それぞれ入力画面と確認画面のみボディを評価する。\n\nパスワード入力では確認用フィールドを入力画面にのみ表示し、携帯電話番号のような項目では確認画面での表示制御を工夫する。\n\n携帯電話番号の場合、エリアコードが入力されていないときはハイフンを表示しないようにしている。\n\nボタンの配置は入力画面と確認画面で異なり、入力画面には確認ボタンを、確認画面には戻るボタンと確定ボタンを配置する構成になっている。\n\nただし、この機能で対応できない場合は、入力画面と確認画面の差異が大きすぎる可能性があるため、別の実装方法を検討する必要がある。\n\n具体的には、入力画面と確認画面のJSPを分けて開発することが適切だ。\n\n確認ページタグを使用すると、確認画面では全ての入力項目がカスタムタグで確認用の出力に切り替わるため、全画面共通ヘッダの検索フォームも確認用として表示される。一方、無視確認タグで囲まれた範囲は常に入力項目として出力されるため、画面内の特定部分だけを常に入力可能な状態に保つことができる。 I'm looking at how to handle form display switching between input and confirmation screens using conditional tags like `n:forInputPage` and `n:forConfirmationPage`, along with specialized input components for passwords and phone numbers, plus controls for button visibility and double-submission prevention. There's also a way to keep certain elements like search forms visible on confirmation screens using `n:ignoreConfirmation`, which reduces the need to duplicate JSP code for confirmation pages.\n\nFor the official documentation URLs, the base URL is empty with no Java documentation references in the source, so I should just return an empty array since there's nothing to include.\n\nNow I need to assemble the JSON output, making sure the sections content is properly escaped as a string. For the images—these are UI screenshots showing implementation results—I'll include them as Markdown image references since they're supplementary to the code examples. Now I'm working through the JSON formatting for the sections, making sure the newlines and quotes are properly escaped. For the first section, I'm capturing the key architectural pattern: when input and confirmation screens map one-to-one, consolidating the JSP implementation reduces the confirmation screen's development effort. The approach keeps the shared logic in the input screen's JSP while the confirmation screen simply forwards to it, and by routing each through separate actions, changes to requirements won't cascade into the action layer. The confirmation screen uses a specific tag for forwarding, and both screens share the same JSP structure.\n\nFor the second section, I'm noting the two custom tags available for controlling which content displays on each screen type.\n\nFor the third section, I'm documenting practical examples: password fields where the confirmation input only appears on the input screen, and mobile phone numbers where formatting is conditionally applied based on whether data exists.\n\nContinuing with the mobile phone example... I'm showing the button configuration for the confirmation page, with a back button to return to the input screen and a register button to finalize the submission, while noting that if the input and confirmation screens differ significantly, it's better to develop them as separate JSP files rather than using this conditional tag approach.\n\nWhen using the ConfirmationPageTag, all custom tags in the confirmation screen output confirmation-formatted content, which means even the common header search form gets rendered as read-only. The IgnoreConfirmationTag lets me place specific input elements inside its body so they always display as interactive form fields regardless of the confirmation state, allowing parts of the screen like a search form to remain functional while the rest shows confirmation output. I'm deciding on the section titles for the index. The expected sections showed empty strings for s1 and s3, which typically indicate intro or continuation content without their own headings, but I think descriptive titles would be more useful for searchability. I'll keep s1 and s3 empty as detected, but use meaningful titles for s2 and s4 to help users find the content they need.\n\nNow I'm preparing to write out the final JSON structure with proper string escaping.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19081,"cache_read_input_tokens":18643,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19081,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eb1c3db-77f7-40a8-82ec-ac177d32be14","uuid":"1f1e7b7a-a083-474b-983c-799a05ab255d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0113242uNnMXXKrYv5spuTSH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_018hLvp8ru5wVnM3Zo9MPpKe","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"id":"libraries-07_FacilitateTag--s1","title":"入力画面と確認画面の共通化をサポートするカスタムタグ","no_knowledge_content":false,"official_doc_urls":[],"index":[{"id":"s1","title":"","hints":["WebView_ConfirmationPageTag","n:confirmationPage","入力画面と確認画面の共通化","確認画面JSP作成工数削減","confirmationPage相対パス指定"]},{"id":"s2","title":"入力画面と確認画面の表示切り替え","hints":["WebView_ForInputPageTag","WebView_ForConfirmationPageTag","n:forInputPage","n:forConfirmationPage","入力画面と確認画面の表示切り替え"]},{"id":"s3","title":"","hints":["n:forInputPage","n:forConfirmationPage","n:password","n:text","n:submit","allowDoubleSubmission","パスワード入力確認","携帯電話番号入力","ボタン表示切り替え"]},{"id":"s4","title":"確認画面での入力項目の表示","hints":["WebView_IgnoreConfirmationTag","n:ignoreConfirmation","共通ヘッダ検索フォーム","確認画面での入力項目表示","ignoreConfirmation"]}],"sections":{"s1":"入力画面と確認画面が1対1に対応する場合、共通化により確認画面JSPの作成工数を削減できる。\n\n実装の共通化は入力画面のJSPで行い、確認画面のJSPは入力画面のJSPにフォワードのみ行う。アクションは入力・確認それぞれ別JSPにフォワードしておくことで、仕様変更時のアクションへの影響を抑えられる。\n\n確認画面のJSPは :ref:`WebView_ConfirmationPageTag` を使用してフォワードを行う。入力・確認画面のJSPは同じ場所に配置することが多いため、相対パスで指定できる。\n\n```jsp\n<%-- USER003.jspは入力画面のJSPとする。 --%>\n<n:confirmationPage path=\"./USER003.jsp\" />\n```","s2":"入力画面と確認画面の表示切り替えには以下のタグを使用する。\n\n| カスタムタグ | 説明 |\n|---|---|\n| :ref:`WebView_ForInputPageTag` | 入力画面のみボディを評価する |\n| :ref:`WebView_ForConfirmationPageTag` | 確認画面のみボディを評価する |","s3":"**パスワードの使用例**\n\n入力画面では確認用の入力項目を2つ表示し、確認画面では一方だけ出力する。\n\n![パスワード入力画面](assets/libraries-07_FacilitateTag--s1/WebView_PasswordInput.jpg)\n\n```jsp\n<n:password name=\"systemAccount.newPassword\" size=\"22\" maxlength=\"20\" />\n<n:forInputPage>\n  <br/>\n  <n:password name=\"systemAccount.confirmPassword\" size=\"22\" maxlength=\"20\" /><span class=\"dinstruct\">(確認用)</span>\n</n:forInputPage>\n```\n\n**携帯電話番号の使用例**\n\n携帯電話番号は全て入力するかしないかの2択であり、確認画面では入力されていない場合にハイフンを表示させないように制御する。\n\n![携帯電話番号入力画面](assets/libraries-07_FacilitateTag--s1/WebView_MobileInput.jpg)\n\n```jsp\n<n:forInputPage>\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberAreaCode\" size=\"5\" maxlength=\"3\" />&nbsp;-&nbsp;\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberCityCode\" size=\"6\" maxlength=\"4\" />&nbsp;-&nbsp;\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberSbscrCode\" size=\"6\" maxlength=\"4\" />\n</n:forInputPage>\n<n:forConfirmationPage>\n  <c:if test=\"${users.mobilePhoneNumberAreaCode != ''}\">\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberAreaCode\" size=\"5\" maxlength=\"3\" />&nbsp;-&nbsp;\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberCityCode\" size=\"6\" maxlength=\"4\" />&nbsp;-&nbsp;\n    <n:text name=\"users.mobilePhoneNumberSbscrCode\" size=\"6\" maxlength=\"4\" />\n  </c:if>\n</n:forConfirmationPage>\n```\n\n**ボタンの使用例**\n\n入力画面は確認ボタン、確認画面は登録画面へ戻るボタンと確定ボタンを表示する。\n\n```jsp\n<n:forInputPage> \n  <n:submit cssClass=\"buttons\" type=\"button\" name=\"confirm\" value=\"確認\" uri=\"/action/ss11AC/W11AC02Action/RW11AC0202\"/> \n</n:forInputPage>\n<n:forConfirmationPage> \n  <n:submit cssClass=\"buttons\" type=\"button\" name=\"back\" value=\"登録画面へ\" uri=\"/action/ss11AC/W11AC02Action/RW11AC0203\"/>\n  <n:submit cssClass=\"buttons\" type=\"button\" name=\"register\" value=\"確定\" uri=\"/action/ss11AC/W11AC02Action/RW11AC0204\" allowDoubleSubmission=\"false\"/>\n</n:forConfirmationPage>\n```\n\n> **重要**: 上記タグで対応できない場合は入力画面と確認画面の差異が多く、この機能の使用に適していない可能性がある。その場合は無理に1つのJSPで作成しようとせずに、入力画面と確認画面のJSPを分けて開発すること。","s4":":ref:`WebView_ConfirmationPageTag` を使用した画面では、確認画面の場合にすべての入力項目のカスタムタグが確認用の出力を行う。そのため、全画面共通ヘッダに検索フォームを配置している場合、その検索フォームも確認用として出力される。\n\n:ref:`WebView_IgnoreConfirmationTag` のボディに配置された入力項目のカスタムタグは常に入力項目として出力される。これにより画面内の一部分を常に入力項目として表示できる。\n\n```jsp\n<%-- ignoreConfirmationタグで囲まれた範囲のみ、常に入力項目として表示される。 --%>\n<n:ignoreConfirmation>\n<n:form>\n  <n:text name=\"searchWords\" />\n  <n:submit type=\"button\" uri=\"./CUSTOM00207\" name=\"CUSTOM00207_submit\" value=\"検索\" />\n</n:form>\n</n:ignoreConfirmation>\n```"}}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19081,"cache_read_input_tokens":18643,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19081,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eb1c3db-77f7-40a8-82ec-ac177d32be14","uuid":"2871015a-e4ff-43e6-92ab-f7c5dbe84d77"}
